    <h3>Three paths that lead to change</h3> <br>
    <p>Throughout our three-year partnership, Malala Fund and Cochlear Foundation we aspire to remove hearing loss as a barrier to life’s <br> opportunities – ensuring girls, children and young people can gain an education and realise their ability to thrive throughout their life. <br> To achieve this, we will: <br><br>
 
     1.	Parents: Appeal to parents to check and if needed, treat their child’s hearing loss from early childhood to make sure hearing loss <br> doesn’t hamper their personal development, ability to access education and realise their full potential. <br><br> 
     
     2.	Hearing health community: Join forces with hearing health non-government organisations (NGOs) and advocacy organisations to <br> collectively raise awareness of the needs of millions of children with hearing loss worldwide. We’ll promote their equal rights to an <br> education and early access to hearing treatment. <br><br>
     
     3.	Governments and societies: Support a growing global call for governments and societies to prioritise hearing health, providing <br> children access to the most appropriate hearing treatments so they can speak, learn, develop and realise their full potential. <br><br>
     
     Just as Malala inspires people everywhere through her amazing story of courage and persistence, we will work alongside Malala Fund <br> to inspire girls, children and young people  with hearing loss, encouraging them to gain an education, build self-esteem and realise <br> their full potential throughout their life. <br> 
     </p>
